    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.\n\nI'd like to have an equivalent to the C `#error` macro that causes Cython compilation to exit immediately with a custom error.\n\nThe motivating case here is letting users see a nice error message instead of a confusing error related to using new Cython features on an old Cython compiler.\n\n@da-woods [suggested](https://github.com/numpy/numpy/pull/30770#issuecomment-3837250926) something like this:\n\n```cython\nDEF err = int('Cython minimum version is 3.0')\n```\n\nWhich works but gives a slightly confusing error message:\n\n```\nddd.pyx:1:13: Error in compile-time expression: ValueError: invalid literal for int() with base 10: 'Cython minimum version is 3.0'\n```\n\n### Describe the solution you'd like.\n\nIt would be nice if future versions of Cython supported something like this:\n\n```\nERROR(\"Cython minimum version is 3.0\")\n```\n\nor perhaps this:\n\n```\n#cython: minimum_cython_version='3.0.0'\n```\n\n### Describe alternatives you've considered.\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional context\n\n_No response_",
